pkg-update-watch
================

pkg-update-watch is a program that will help you keeping your system up to date.
pkg-update-watch checks if package updates are available and sends a report of 
available update by mail or on standard output.

To use pkg-update-watch, add the following line in the root crontab file:

0 0 * * * /opt/csw/bin/pkg-update-watch --mail

You can configure mail report recipients and report filters in 
/opt/csw/etc/pkg-update-watch.conf. 

